Patrick J. Siewert
Senior Consultant


Download vCard

Cellular Call Detail Record Analysis and Mapping, Computer and Digital Forensic Analysis, GPS Forensic Data Acquisition and Reporting, Internet-Based Investigation, Mobile Device Forensics, Technical Investigation







Experience
A licensed private investigator and certified law enforcement instructor, Mr. Siewert has 15 years of experience in law enforcement highlighted by precedent-setting work in electronic and high-tech criminal investigations and digital and computer forensics. His expertise extends to mobile device forensics, cellular call detail record analysis, and online undercover investigations. Mr. Siewert has been trained and certified by multiple governmental entities, including the U.S. Secret Service, U.S. Dept. of Homeland Security, National White Collar Crime Center, and the Public Agency Training Council, as well as multiple digital forensic software providers. Mr. Siewert is a principal consultant for Professional Digital Forensic Consulting, LLC based in Central Virginia, offering forensic data acquisition, analysis, reporting and consulting. He regularly authors technical articles on topics of digital forensics and investigation, and is a frequent technology contributor for multiple media outlets. Mr. Siewert serves as a court-certified expert witness, providing expert consulting and litigation support on cases involving cellular, digital, computer and Internet forensics, records analysis, and technology.


Credentials

Licensed Private Investigator, Virginia
+SMART Smartphone Forensics and Cellular Technology Certification
Lantern Certified Examiner – Katana Forensics
Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services General Instructor – Law Enforcement
BS, Criminal Justice, Virginia Commonwealth University, 1999
Seized Computer Evidence Recovery Specialist, Federal Law Enforcement Training Center
Basic Computer Evidence Recovery Training, National Computer Forensics Institute, United States Secret Service
Basic Data Recovery and Acquisition, National White Collar Crime Center
Intermediate Data Recovery and Analysis, National White Collar Crime Center
EnCase Forensics, Level 1 & Level 2
X-Ways Integrated Forensics Level 1



Affiliations/Awards

International Association of Computer Investigative Specialists, Member
High-Tech Crime Investigator’s Association, Member
